byg.commands.repairbiomesource.warning1: !_1.18_Warning: you are about to change this world's Nether and/or End Biome Sources to BYG's Nether and/or End Biome sources. It is HIGHLY recommended you make a backup of your world before you proceed. Copy your world's "level.dat" file(found in here: %s) to a separate directory. Then run this command again.
byg.commands.repairbiomesource.warning2:
!_1.18_Did you backup your "level.dat"? Because you are about to change this world's Nether and/or End Biome Sources to BYG's Nether and/or End Biomes sources. It is HIGHLY recommended you make a backup of your world's "level.dat" file before you proceed. Copy your world's "level.dat" file(found in here: %s) to a separate directory. Then run this command again.
If the command succeeds, your server will close/you will be exited from your world.
byg.end.not.used:
!_1.18_Warning: You are receiving this warning because BYG's End Biome Source is not being used in this world's End and therefore renders BYG's end config useless. Your config specifies it should be using it! If this is intentional(ie using another end mod), you may disable this warning from appearing in future worlds by visiting your config found here: "%s" and setting "warnBYGEndBiomeSourceNotUsedInNewWorlds" to "false"!
If this is not intentional please follow the instructions found here: %s to enable BYG's end.
byg.experimental.warning: !_1.18_You are currently using an experimental or an incomplete version of BYG. Worlds are bound to break or bug if you update BYG in this world!
